<p><img src="https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/f/c/8/event_515685000.jpeg" border="0" /><br /><br /><strong>Narrowing the skills gap, one chapter at a time.</strong><br /><br />Welcome to <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/events/295936986/">Front-End Development Bootcamp</a></strong>. We have begun.</p>
<p><strong>The Scoreboard</strong></p>
<p>~ 32 Boston PHP members signed up for Bootcamp<br />~ 5 members have made the commitment to begin by posting to <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/boards/thread/53966604/">Introduce Yourself</a></strong><br />~ 0 members have completed Sprint #1 &gt; <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53972219">Introduction to HTML</a></strong></p>
<p>The first step is to gain access to <strong><a href="https://frontendmasters.com/bootcamp/">Bootcamp Learning Path</a></strong>—a FREE series of training modules offered by <strong>Frontend Masters</strong>.</p>
<p>The second step is to post a brief update to <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53966604">Introduce Yourself</a></strong> which will acknowledge your commitment to begin this training opportunity.</p>
<p>This week launches <strong>Sprint #2</strong>. The target is to begin <strong>Introduction to CSS</strong>, the second of nine modules in this Bootcamp. This module should take a little more than four hours to complete. Two weekly sprints have been allotted for this module. Once finished, post an update to <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53981181">Bootcamp: Introduction to CSS</a></strong>.</p>
<p>For a complete list of all Modules and Sprint dates, access <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53971585">Master Discussion List—Front-End Development Bootcamp</a></strong>. Feel free to post whatever questions you might have in the <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53966604">Introduce Yourself</a></strong> discussion area.</p>
<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> I have adjusted the event on Meetup to continue registration through the end of September. Feel free to invite your tech-friendly friends and co-workers to join you on this Bootcamp journey.</p>
<p>Gene Babon<br />Co-Organizer &amp; Chief Percolator<br /><strong>Boston PHP Meetup</strong> &amp; <strong><a href="https://webapprentices.org/about-web-apprentices/">Web Apprentices<br /></a></strong></p>
